{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646053","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646053"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:25:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:25:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18151"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18151","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18151"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.26,0.06,0.48,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10865"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73659"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10865","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10865"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18151"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59132"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"5325"},{"type":"tags","id":"7230"},{"type":"tags","id":"7331"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25274"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25277"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73659","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73659"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is not supplied by the ulnar nerve in the hand?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hypothenar muscles","Adductor pollicis","All interossei","2nd lumbrical","3rd lumbrical"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe ulnar nerve is responsible for innervating most of the intrinsic muscles of the hand, including the \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypothenar muscles\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eadductor pollicis\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003Eall interossei\u003C/strong\u003E. These muscles are crucial for fine motor control and movements such as finger abduction and adduction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003E2nd lumbrical\u003C/strong\u003E is not supplied by the ulnar nerve; it is innervated by the median nerve. The median nerve supplies the first and second lumbricals, which are involved in flexing the metacarpophalangeal joints and extending the interphalangeal joints of the index and middle fingers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003E3rd lumbrical\u003C/strong\u003E is supplied by the ulnar nerve, along with the fourth lumbrical. These lumbricals assist in similar movements for the ring and little fingers.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The ulnar nerve supplies most of the intrinsic muscles of the hand, including the hypothenar muscles, adductor pollicis, and interossei.","The ulnar nerve does not supply the first and second lumbricals, which are innervated by the median nerve."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Raszewski JA, Black AC, Launico MV, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Hand Compartments. [Updated 2023 Oct 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/books/NBK532942/","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences250"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59132"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18151"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59132","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59132"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T01:09:07+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T01:09:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10865"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73659"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4930","links":{"self"